				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
									<p id="u648469-2">The DWR Round is a desktop wraparound labelling machine developed for accurate applications of self-adhesive labels on cylindrical packaging. The DWR Round can accept labels of up to and including 200mm width, the roller can be adjusted to any core type which can accept label rolls of up to 300mm in diameter, therefore reducing downtime. The DWR Round can apply wraparound or individual front and back labels to all types of cylindrical packaging. The labels are initiated by a fork photocell that detects the leading edge of each label.</p><p id="u648469-5">The DWR Round can be equipped with an ultrasonic sensor which is able to read the difference in thickness between the labels and the liner when applying transparent labels. In addition an inkjet coder can also be attached for printing variable data for traceability. The coder is able to print times, dates, barcodes and text with a maximum height of up to 12.7mm at 300dpi with the text being supplied on software included, in addition to this the coder can also be synchronised to the same speed of the label feed.</p><p><span style="color: #000000;"><strong>Specification</strong></span></p><div id="u633640-17" class="clearfix grpelem shared_content" data-muse-uid="U633640" data-muse-type="txt_frame" data-ibe-flags="txtStyleSrc" data-content-guid="u633640-17_content"><ul id="u633640-15" class="list0 nls-None"><li id="u633640-2">Stepper motor drives for product rotation</li><li id="u633640-4">Full wraparound or Front and back label</li><li id="u633640-6">Label unwind unit for reels up to 300mm</li><li id="u633640-8">200mm maximum web width capability</li><li id="u633640-10">Can handle bottles from 20mm to 130mm</li><li id="u633640-12">Left or right hand versions available</li><li id="u633640-14">Variable dispensing speed</li><li>Quick and easy change between labels</li><li>Supplied with motorised product jig assembly</li><li>Ready to plug in and use immediately</li></ul></div>								</div>
				</div>
